## Summary

- Add `src/compiler/incremental/` package wrapping the compiler pipeline with [mizchi/ripple](https://github.com/mizchi/ripple) (salsa-inspired incremental computation)
- When file source is unchanged, cached compile returns in **~0.3µs** vs **~130-680µs** for full recompilation
- Foundation for future watch mode and IDE integration

### Benchmark: direct vs incremental (2nd+ build)

| Benchmark | Direct (every call) | Incremental (cached) | Speedup |
|---|---|---|---|
| basic | 136 µs | **0.31 µs** | **438x** |
| composable | 679 µs | **0.31 µs** | **2190x** |

### Query graph

```
Input[file_sources] → Query[sfc]      → Query[template]
                                       → Query[css]
                    → Query[compile]   (full pipeline)
```

### API

```moonbit
let ic = IncrementalCompiler::new()
ic.set_source("App.mbtv", source)  // returns false if unchanged
ic.compile("App.mbtv")             // cached on 2nd+ call
ic.get_sfc("App.mbtv")             // fine-grained cached queries
ic.get_template("App.mbtv")
ic.get_css("App.mbtv")
```

